# IP Address Manager

A web-based management tool for Box 9's LED receivers and network device. Tracks receivers (IP + MAC addresses), groups them into devices, assigns devices to players, monitors live reachability, and optionally manages a dnsmasq DHCP configuration.

## Data model

```
Player  →  Device  →  Receiver
```

| Entity | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Player** | Top-level grouping (e.g. a video player) |
| **Device** | A logical device belonging to a player |
| **Receiver** | An networked receiver or device with a unique name, IP address, and MAC address |

## Features

- **CRUD** for Receivers, Devices, and Players via a server-rendered HTML UI (FastAPI + Jinja2 + HTMX)
- **Live ping monitor** — real-time reachability status for all receivers streamed over WebSocket
- **dnsmasq integration** — writes DHCP host entries from receiver MAC/IP data and manages the dnsmasq service via `systemctl`
- Inline validation and conflict detection (duplicate name, IP, MAC) with per-field error messages returned as HTMX partial swaps

## Tech stack

| Layer | Library |
|-------|---------|
| Web framework | FastAPI |
| ORM / models | SQLModel (SQLite by default) |
| Templates | Jinja2 + HTMX |
| Validation | Pydantic v2 |
| Async ping | asyncio |
| Real-time | WebSockets |

## Dev workflows

```bash
# Install dependencies
poetry install

# Run dev server (auto-reload)
poetry run uvicorn app.app:app --host 0.0.0.0 --reload

# Run production server
poetry run uvicorn app.app:app --host 0.0.0.0

# Run tests
poetry run pytest

# Run tests with coverage
poetry run pytest --cov=app
```

## Configuration

Environment variables (`.env` file or shell):

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `DB_LOCATION` | `./ip_manager.db` | Path to the SQLite database file |
| `DNSMASQ_DHCP_CONF_PATH` | *(unset)* | Path to the dnsmasq DHCP config file; dnsmasq integration is disabled when unset |
| `DNSMASQ_SERVICE_NAME` | `dnsmasq` | systemd service name for dnsmasq |
| `DNSMASQ_SYSTEMCTL_PATH` | `systemctl` | Path to the `systemctl` binary |
| `DNSMASQ_LEASE_FILE` | *(unset)* | Path to the dnsmasq lease file; omitted from config when unset |
| `DNSMASQ_ADDRESS` | `/box9pi.box9/192.168.1.1` | dnsmasq `address=` directive written to the config; set to empty string to omit |

## Project structure

```
app/
  app.py                  # FastAPI app wiring, router registration
  db.py                   # Engine, session, table creation
  models/                 # SQLModel table definitions
  crud/                   # Database operations (raise domain errors on failure)
  webapp_routes/          # FastAPI routers (thin — delegate to crud/)
  services/               # dnsmasq manager, ping manager, WebSocket hub
  templates/              # Jinja2 HTML templates and HTMX partials
  utils/                  # Exceptions, form parsing, validation formatting
tests/
  crud/                   # CRUD unit tests (in-memory SQLite)
  routes/                 # Route integration tests (TestClient + in-memory SQLite)
  models/                 # Model validation tests
  services/               # Service unit tests
  utils/                  # Utility unit tests
```

